ZeroCore Bot Privacy Policy

Last updated: July 6 2026

ZeroCore Bot only uses the information required to provide its server management features.

The bot may process Discord user IDs server IDs channel IDs role IDs usernames and ticket messages when users interact with ticket or moderation features.

This information is used only for bot functionality such as creating tickets setting up roles managing channels and keeping the server organized.

ZeroCore Bot does not sell personal data share personal data with advertisers or use data for tracking outside Discord.

Ticket messages may be visible to authorized server staff depending on the server configuration.

Server owners may remove the bot from their server at any time. If data deletion is needed users can contact the bot owner or server administration team.

ZeroCore Bot follows Discord Terms of Service Community Guidelines and Developer Policy.
